The paper deals with image set matching, which is a problem in computer vision. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also proposes a novel approach that involves clustering and classification, which falls under the sub-categories of machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also uses datasets to evaluate the proposed method, which falls under the sub-category of multimedia (cs.MM). Finally, the paper deals with matching image sets, which can be considered a problem in information retrieval (cs.IR).
